        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 4:24PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 424 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Springer, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Springer and Abbott.

This includes Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 403 and 425.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
